I finally managed to find the solution:

When an array is passed as an argument into a GraphQL query, be it as the input itself or as a field of an object type ([GraphQL-Java Doc][1]), Spring converts it not to an *array* but to a *list*, hence the cryptic binding error.

Hence the problem was solved by simply changing the field from *String[]* to *List\&lt;String\&gt;*.

    public class MyArray {

      public MyArray(String[] arr){
        this.arr = arr;
      }

      private String[] arr;

      public String[] getArr() {
        return arr;
    }

changed to:

    public class MyArray {

      public MyArray(List&lt;String&gt; arr){
        this.arr = arr;
      }

      private List&lt;String&gt; arr;

      public List&lt;String&gt; getArr() {
        return arr;
    }


  [1]: https://www.graphql-java.com/documentation/data-mapping/#lists-of-input-types

